 Buttigieg filed a request for a recanvass of 66 precincts and Sanders for 28 precincts, the party said in a statement. It said it will review the requests to determine whether they meet the requirements. Buttigieg had a slim lead over Sanders in the Feb. 3 nominating contest, which took days to settle after a technical meltdown led to delays in determining the winner. (Reporting by Doina Chiacu; Editing by Lisa Lambert) Please note you must be a Maverick Insider to comment. Sign up here or sign in if you are already an Insider.